
Overview of noun breath

The noun breath has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (15) breath -- (the process of taking in and expelling air during breathing; "he took a deep breath and dived into the pool"; "he was fighting to his last breath")
2. (14) breath -- (the air that is inhaled and exhaled in respiration; "his sour breath offended her")
3. (1) breath, breather, breathing place, breathing space, breathing spell, breathing time -- (a short respite)
4. (1) hint, intimation, breath -- (an indirect suggestion; "not a breath of scandal ever touched her")
5. breath -- (a slight movement of the air; "there wasn't a breath of air in the room")
